# Todo CLI

A Python command-line interface application for managing todos.

## Features

- Add new tasks with titles and optional descriptions
- List all tasks with their completion status
- Update existing tasks
- Mark tasks as complete/incomplete
- Delete tasks
- Cross-platform support

## Requirements

- Python 3.13 or higher

## Installation

1. Clone the repository:
   ```bash
   git clone <repository-url>
   cd todo-cli
   ```

2. Install the package:
   ```bash
   pip install .
   ```

   Or for development:
   ```bash
   pip install -e .
   ```

## Usage

### Adding a Task
```bash
todo add "Buy groceries" --description "Milk, bread, eggs"
```

### Listing All Tasks
```bash
todo list
```

### Updating a Task
```bash
todo update <task-id> --title "New title" --description "New description"
```

### Marking a Task Complete
```bash
todo complete <task-id>
```

### Marking a Task Incomplete
```bash
todo incomplete <task-id>
```

### Deleting a Task
```bash
todo delete <task-id>
```

## Examples

```bash
# Add a task
todo add "Complete project proposal"

# Add a task with description
todo add "Review code" --description "Review the new feature implementation"

# List all tasks
todo list

# Mark a task as complete
todo complete 123e4567-e89b-12d3-a456-426614174000

# Update a task
todo update 123e4567-e89b-12d3-a456-426614174000 --title "Updated task title"

# Delete a task
todo delete 123e4567-e89b-12d3-a456-426614174000
```

## Development

### Running Tests

```bash
# Run all tests
pytest

# Run unit tests
pytest tests/unit/

# Run integration tests
pytest tests/integration/

# Run with coverage
pytest --cov=src/
```

### Project Structure

```
src/
├── models/          # Data models
│   └── task.py
├── services/        # Business logic
│   └── todo_service.py
├── cli/             # Command-line interface
│   └── todo_cli.py
├── app.py          # Main application entry point
└── __init__.py

tests/
├── unit/           # Unit tests
│   ├── models/
│   └── services/
└── integration/    # Integration tests
    └── cli/
```

## Architecture

The application follows clean architecture principles:

- **Models**: Data representation and validation
- **Services**: Business logic and operations
- **CLI**: User interface and command parsing
- **Repositories**: Data access abstraction (not fully implemented in Phase 1)

